Again similar three-electrodes setup was used for the evaluation of HER performance but in nitrogen-saturated 1 M KOH electrolyte solution. This time, the working electrode was prepared by depositing the electrocatalyst ink on the disk of the rotating disk electrode (RDE, E5 series) with a disk area of 0.1963 cm2, operating at 1600 rpm. Electrocatalyst loading of 0.6 mg cm−2 was used to prepare the working electrode. The potential window for acquiring the LSVs (at the scan rate of 5 mV s−1) for HER was maintained between − 1.05 and − 2.05 V vs SCE. During the testing, nitrogen gas was continuously purged in the electrolyte. Eventually, all the potential values were converted into reversible hydrogen potential using the following relationship:3ERHE=ESCE+E0SCE+0.0591×pH.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
